6 Sec. 204. A department or agency shall use the internet to
7 fulfill the reporting requirements of this part and shall make each
8 report readily accessible to the public and conspicuously post each
9 required report in a single archivable location on the department's
10 or agency's Michigan.gov website not later than the due date
11 required for each report. In addition to placing all reports
12 required in the current fiscal year on the department's or agency's
13 website, the department or agency shall maintain on its website all
14 reports placed on the website from previous fiscal years posted by
15 fiscal year in the same single archivable location. The department
16 or agency shall also transmit all required reports for the current
17 fiscal year to the standard recipients and any other required
18 recipients by email.
