15 Sec. 203. As used in this part and part 1:
16 (a) "Administrative segregation" means confinement for
17 maintenance of order or discipline to a cell or room apart from
18 accommodations provided for inmates who are participating in
19 programs of the facility.
20 (b) "Department" means the department of corrections.
21 (c) "Director" means the director of the department.
22 (d) "DOJ" means the United States Department of Justice.
23 (e) "DOJ-BOP" means the DOJ Bureau of Prisons.
24 (f) "Evidence-based" means a decision-making process that
25 integrates the best available research, clinician expertise, and
26 client characteristics.
27 (g) "FTE" means full-time equated position in the classified
28 service of this state.
29 (h) "Goal" means the intended or projected result of a
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

56
1 comprehensive corrections plan or community corrections program to
2 reduce repeat offending, criminogenic and high-risk behaviors,
3 prison commitment rates, the length of stay in a jail, or to
4 improve the utilization of a jail.
5 (i) "Jail" means a facility operated by a local unit of
6 government for the physical detention and correction of individuals
7 charged with or convicted of criminal offenses.
8 (j) "OCC" means the office of community corrections.
9 (k) "Offender success" means that an offender has, with the
10 support of the community, intervention of the field agent, and
11 benefit of any participation in programs and treatment, made an
12 adjustment while at liberty in the community such that the offender
13 has not been sentenced to or returned to prison for the conviction
14 of a new crime or the revocation of probation or parole.
15 (l) "Recidivism" means that term as defined in section 1 of
16 2017 PA 5, MCL 798.31.
17 (m) "Serious emotional disturbance" means that term as defined
18 in section 100d(3) of the mental health code, 1974 PA 258, MCL
19 330.1100d.
20 (n) "Serious mental illness" means that term as defined in
21 section 100d(4) of the mental health code, 1974 PA 258, MCL
22 330.1100d.
23 (o) "SSA" means the United States Social Security
24 Administration.
25 (p) "SSA-SSI" means SSA supplemental security income.
