8 Sec. 959. (1) The department of treasury shall distribute
9 funds appropriated in part 1 for public safety revenue sharing
10 grants as provided for in subsection (9) and as follows:
11 (a) $3,250,000.00 to the MDHHS to establish and administer a
12 grant program to award funds to community violence intervention
13 programs.
14 (b) $35,062,500.00 for a public safety assistance payment to
15 each city, village, or township. The public safety assistance
16 payment must be calculated as follows:
17 (i) Determine the average violent crime count for each city,
18 village, and township by adding the 2 highest annual violent crime
19 counts for each city, village, and township from the 3 most
20 recently available annual crime reports published by the MDSP as of
21 the first day of the current fiscal year and dividing by 2.
22 (ii) Determine the statewide total violent crime count by
23 summing the average violent crime count for each city, village, and
24 township as determined under subparagraph (i).
25 (iii) Determine the proportional factor for each city, village,
26 and township by dividing the average violent crime count for each
27 city, village, and township as determined under subparagraph (i) by
28 the statewide total violent crime count determined under
29 subparagraph (ii).
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

304
1 (iv) Multiply the proportional factor determined in
2 subparagraph (iii), for each city, village, and township by the total
3 amount available for distribution under this subdivision, and round
4 to the nearest dollar.
5 (2) A public safety assistance payment to a city, village, or
6 township as determined under subsection (1)(b) is limited to not
7 more than 25% of the total amount available for distribution under
8 subsection (1)(b).
9 (3) All of the following apply to a distribution under
10 subsection (1)(b):
11 (a) A city, village, or township must use the distribution
12 only for operational and capital expenditures that serve the
13 purposes of public safety.
