15 or section 991(1) of article 5 of 2025 PA 22.
16 (3) The amount of adjustment grants to each county that is
17 qualified under subsection (2) must be calculated in the following
18 manner:
19 (a) For county prosecutors that received an amount under
20 section 991 of article 5 of 2023 PA 119 that was greater than the
21 amount received in section 805 of article 16 of 2025 PA 22 and
22 section 991(1) of article 5 of 2025 PA 22, the amount must be the
23 sum of the amount received in section 991 of article 5 of 2023 PA
24 119 minus the amount received under section 805 of article 16 of
25 2025 PA 22, plus the amount received in section 991 of article 5 of
26 2023 PA 119 minus the amount received under section 991(1) of
27 article 5 of 2025 PA 22.
28 (b) For county prosecutors that received an amount under
29 section 805 of article 16 of 2025 PA 22 that was greater than the
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

317
1 amount received under section 991(1) of article 5 of 2025 PA 22,
2 the amount calculated must be the amount received in section 805 of
3 article 16 of 2025 PA 22 minus the amount received under section
4 991(1) of article 5 of 2025 PA 22.
5 Sec. 994. (1) From the funds appropriated in part 1 for
6 municipal infrastructure grants, the department of treasury shall
7 create and operate a grant program to award competitive grants to
8 cities, villages, townships, and counties to upgrade municipal
9 facilities that are at least 50 years old.
10 (2) The department of treasury shall prioritize cities,
11 villages, townships, or counties that have 1 or more conditions
12 that indicate probable financial distress as determined by the
13 department of treasury under section 956.
14 (3) The department of treasury shall award not more than
15 $1,000,000.00 to any city, village, township, or county and shall
16 require that the grant recipient commit at least 25% of the amount
17 received to the project.
18 (4) Not later than March 31, the department of treasury shall
19 submit a report to the standard report recipients that includes all
20 of the following for each grant recipient:
21 (a) The name of the grant recipient.
22 (b) The date the grant was approved.
23 (c) The amount of the grant.
24 (d) A description of the project or projects that will be paid
25 by the grant.
26 Sec. 995. (1) For a public safety academy assistance grant
27 program, the funds appropriated under this subsection must be used
28 by the Michigan commission on law enforcement standards to do all
29 of the following:
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

318
1 (a) Administer a competitive public safety academy assistance
2 scholarship program that provides police academy scholarships of
3 not more than $20,000.00 per recruit on a first-come, first-served
4 basis to an individual who meets the requirements of subsection (2)
5 and any necessary requirements to enroll in a police academy
6 program.
7 (b) Pay the salaries of training academy recruits from local
8 public safety agencies or to pay the salaries of police cadets who
9 are receiving tuition assistance under subsection (2) and academy
10 tuition and eligible related costs as determined by the Michigan
11 commission on law enforcement standards.
12 (2) In order to receive a scholarship under subsection (1)(a),
13 an individual must have applied to at least 1 law enforcement basic
14 training academy approved by the Michigan commission on law
15 enforcement standards, have completed an interview, and have
16 received approval for the scholarship from the public safety agency
17 that the individual intends to serve.
18 (3) For the purposes of subsection (1)(a), not more than 25
19 scholarships may be approved for a particular public safety agency.
20 (4) The Michigan commission on law enforcement standards may
21 use not more than $140,000.00 for administration of the scholarship
22 program established and administered by the Michigan commission on
23 law enforcement standards under subsection (1).
24 (5) The Michigan commission on law enforcement standards may
25 set any necessary additional requirements for the distribution of
26 the funds disbursed under subsection (1).
