29 Sec. 1100. (1) Subject to section 242 of the management and
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

319
1 budget act, 1984 PA 431, MCL 18.1242, and on the approval of the
2 state building authority, the department of treasury may expend
3 from the general fund of this state during the fiscal year an
4 amount necessary to meet the cash flow requirements of those state
5 building authority projects solely for lease to a state agency
6 identified in both part 1 and this section, and for which state
7 building authority bonds or notes have not been issued, and for the
8 sole acquisition by the state building authority of equipment and
9 furnishings for lease to a state agency as permitted by 1964 PA
10 183, MCL 830.411 to 830.425, for which the issuance of bonds or
11 notes is authorized by an appropriations PA that is effective for
12 the immediately preceding fiscal year. Any general fund advances
13 for which state building authority bonds have not been issued must
14 bear an interest cost to the state building authority at a rate
15 that is not greater than the rate earned by the state treasurer's
16 common cash fund during the period in which the advances are
17 outstanding and are repaid to the general fund of this state.
18 (2) On sale of bonds or notes for the projects identified in
19 part 1 or for equipment as authorized by an appropriations PA and
20 in this section, the state building authority shall credit the
21 general fund of this state an amount equal to the amount expended
22 from the general fund plus interest, if any, as described in this
23 section.
24 (3) For state building authority projects for which bonds or
25 notes have been issued and on the request of the state building
26 authority, the state treasurer shall make advances without interest
27 from the general fund as necessary to meet cash flow requirements
28 for the projects. The state building authority shall reimburse the
29 state treasurer for the advances when the investments earmarked for
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

320
1 the financing of the projects mature.
2 (4) If a project identified in part 1 is terminated after
3 final design is complete, advances made on behalf of the state
4 building authority for the costs of final design must be repaid to
