6 state building authority.
7 Sec. 1102. (1) The state building authority shall not release
8 state building authority funding to a university or community
9 college to finance the construction or renovation of a facility
10 that collects revenue in excess of money required for the operation
11 of that facility unless the university or community college agrees
12 to use that excess revenue to reimburse the state building
13 authority. The excess revenue received by the state building
14 authority as reimbursement must be credited to the general fund to
15 offset rent obligations associated with the retirement of bonds
16 issued for the applicable facility. The auditor general shall
17 annually identify and audit the facilities that are subject to this
18 section. Costs associated with the administration of the audit must
19 be charged against money received by the state building authority
20 as reimbursement under this section.
21 (2) As used in this section, "revenue" includes state
22 appropriations, facility opening money, other state aid, indirect
23 cost reimbursement, and other revenue generated by the activities
24 of the facility.
25 Sec. 1103. Not later than October 15, the state building
26 authority shall submit a report to the standard report recipients
27 and the JCOS regarding the status of construction projects
28 associated with state building authority bonds as of the end of the
29 immediately preceding fiscal year. Not later than 30 days after a
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

321
1 refinancing or restructuring bond issue is sold, the state building
2 authority shall submit a report to the standard report recipients
3 and the JCOS regarding the status of construction projects
4 associated with that bond issue. Each report must include all of
5 the following:
6 (a) A list of all completed construction projects for which
7 state building authority bonds have been sold, and which bonds are
8 currently active.
9 (b) A list of all projects under construction for which sale
10 of state building authority bonds is pending.
11 (c) A list of all projects authorized for construction or
12 identified in an appropriations act for which approval of
13 schematic/preliminary plans or total authorized cost is pending
14 that have state building authority bonds identified as a source of
15 financing.
