3 Sec. 1180. From the funds appropriated in part 1 for
4 epidemiology administration and for childhood lead program, the
5 department shall maintain a public health drinking water program
6 and maintain enhanced efforts to monitor child blood lead levels.
7 The public health drinking water program shall ensure that
8 appropriate investigations of potential health hazards occur for
9 all community and noncommunity drinking water supplies where
10 chemical exceedances of action levels, health advisory levels, or
11 maximum contaminant limits are identified. The goals of the
12 childhood lead program must include improving the identification of
13 children affected by lead exposure, improving the timeliness of
14 case follow-up, and attaining nurse care management for children
15 with lead exposure, and to achieve a long-term reduction in the
16 percentage of children in this state with elevated blood lead
17 levels.
