4 automobile insurance rate setting, including the use of these
5 embedded into rate or premium setting calculations and formulas.
6 (b) A model if each individual factor was removed as well as
7 if all factors were removed.
8 (c) The relationship of non-driving factors to uninsured
9 motorist numbers in the state.
10 (d) The relationship of uninsured motorists on statewide
11 rates.
12 (e) A comparison with other states and the impact on their
13 rates that have eliminated non-driving factors.
14 (f) A clear outline of methods and assumptions made in the
15 report.
16 (2) Non-driving factors that the report must study include,
