18 (a) Credit scores or insurance scores.
19 (b) Gender or sex.
20 (c) Occupation.
21 (d) Income level.
22 (e) Geographic location.
23 (f) Age.
24 (g) Education level attained.
25 (h) Homeownership.
26 (i) Territories more impacted by the use of non-driving
