18 or eliminate due to the lost revenue.
19 (iii) The anticipated fiscal impact on residents of this state.
20 (b) Affect an industry, community, population, or other group
21 regulated or served by, or that otherwise engages with, the
22 department or agency.
23 (c) Create a regulatory gap that could negatively impact the
24 public.
25 (d) Increase the department's or agency's costs.
