1 Sec. 528. (1) The funds appropriated in part 1 for job
2 creation services shall support the office of small business growth
3 within the Michigan economic development corporation to lead,
4 coordinate, and administer statewide programs, services, and
5 investments that support the launch, resilience, and growth of
6 small businesses in this state, including a focus on and support
7 for microbusinesses.
8 (2) The office shall serve as this state's primary point of
9 coordination for small business development, technical assistance,
10 access to capital, and cross-agency small business initiatives.
11 (3) The office shall perform duties under this section that
12 include all of the following:
13 (a) Develop and enhance a statewide, collaborative, public-
14 private partner network to accelerate small business formation,
15 resilience, and scale.
16 (b) Administer grants, loans, and investments to
17 organizations, intermediaries, and subject-matter experts that
18 provide technical assistance, coaching, consulting, training, or
19 other services that support small business success.
20 (c) Administer grants, loans, and investments directly to
21 Michigan-headquartered small businesses to advance strategic
22 company or industry growth objectives, including supply chain
23 resiliency, clean energy integration, technology adoption, and
24 global competitiveness.
25 (d) Coordinate with lenders, financial institutions, industry
26 partners, and other key stakeholders to strengthen and expand
27 access to capital for small businesses, including addressing
28 industry, regional, and demographic gaps in lending, enhancing
29 capital readiness, and supporting innovative financing models that
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

605
1 improve small business growth and resilience.
2 (e) Lead cross-agency coordination with relevant state
3 departments to improve small business navigation of state
4 resources, regulatory processes, and programs connected to business
5 launch, resilience, and expansion.
6 (f) Align small business services with this state's broader
7 entrepreneurship, innovation, and economic development strategies,
8 including leveraging state and federal funding, data, evaluation,
9 and ecosystem-building efforts.
10 (g) Collect and analyze data to monitor program effectiveness,
11 vendor and partner impact, and small business outcomes, and ensure
12 transparency and accountability through public reporting.
13 (h) Create, implement, and update a statewide strategic plan
14 for creation and distribution of economic growth services focused
15 on economic gardening. This plan must be developed and maintained
16 with ongoing engagement with regionally representative
17 stakeholders.
18 (4) The office may enter into agreements, contracts, or
19 partnerships with public, private, nonprofit, philanthropic, and
20 academic partners necessary to carry out the responsibilities under
21 this section and to implement programs and initiatives supporting
22 small business development statewide.
23 (5) The office may establish eligibility criteria, application
24 processes, compliance requirements, and reporting standards for
25 recipients of funds administered under this section.
26 (6) The office shall submit an annual report to the standard
