15 support a local talent plan, including other governmental funds or
16 private resources.
17 (8) In addition to the eligible activities under subsection
18 (7), approved local talent plans must include all of the following:
19 (a) A defined area, such as a neighborhood, district, or
20 corridor, in which a local talent plan will be implemented. Unless
21 identified as a supporting part of an approved talent plan, funds
22 allocated to approved plans must be used only within the plan's
23 defined area.
24 (b) A description of how local talent plan activities directly
25 support the objectives under subsection (2).
26 (c) A description of how funds appropriated under part 1 for
27 talent partnership will be used and any other funds or resources
28 that will be provided to ensure a plan meets all the objectives
29 under subsection (2).
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

650
1 (d) Identification of stakeholders that were engaged in the
2 development and are committed to the implementation of a local
3 talent plan.
4 (e) In addition to any state or federal resources,
5 identification of local or private match funds or resources that
6 will be committed.
7 (f) A proposed implementation timeline and demonstration of a
8 local talent plan's sustainability after any state or federal funds
9 are exhausted.
10 (g) Identifiable goals and measurable outcomes to be used to
11 monitor progress.
12 (9) To leverage existing programs and resources to support
13 talent concentration, the department may establish a state agency
14 workgroup to support the implementation of this section, including
15 from agencies that oversee any programs related to housing, home
16 repairs, blight elimination, business supports, community
17 development, transportation or mobility, arts, and outdoor
18 recreation.
19 (10) The department may retain up to 3% of funds under this
20 section for implementation costs. In addition, the department may
21 retain up to an additional 2% of funds under this section to
22 reimburse other state agencies' activities that are in support of a
23 talent partnership project. The department may contract with at
24 least 1 consultant that is a nonprofit research organization or
25 public education institution based in this state with experience in
26 at least placemaking research to support this section.
27 (11) The department shall post online the guidelines for local
28 talent plans and identify available research or resources that may
29 be used to support the development of a local talent plan.
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

651
1 (12) In evaluating each application, subject to subsection
2 (13), the department shall use objective criteria, including, but
3 not limited to, the comprehensive nature of the local talent plan,
4 the local support identified, long-term sustainability, and the
5 likelihood to achieve the goals of the talent partnership program.
6 The department must consider, but is not limited to, all of the
7 following when selecting grant recipients:
8 (a) The extent to which a proposed local talent plan will
9 support the creation and ongoing success of locally owned
10 businesses.
11 (b) The extent to which a proposed local talent plan will
12 create dense, walkable, vibrant spaces.
13 (c) The extent to which zoning and code restrictions have
14 been, or will need to be, modified to support high-density
15 residential development.
16 (d) The extent to which the proposed local talent plan
17 supports facilities and walkways that house or present cultural
18 arts programs, performances, and exhibitions.
19 (e) The extent to which the proposed local talent plan
20 provides mixed-income housing.
21 (f) The likelihood of successful implementation of a proposed
22 plan and its sustainability.
23 (13) The department shall award funds consistent with the
24 following:
25 (a) Grants must be awarded in a geographically diverse manner.
26 (b) Subject to the department's approval, the grant program
27 permits grant awards to continue implementation of existing talent
28 plans.
29 (14) The department shall publish approved local talent plans
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

652
1 and funding allocations under this section on the department's
2 website. The department may approve subsequent rounds of funding
3 for local talent plans if either additional funds become available
