4 Sec. 411. (1) From the funds appropriated in part 1 for
5 veterans service grants, the MVAA shall establish, administer, and
6 award competitive grants to 1 or more congressionally chartered
7 VSOs or a coalition of VSOs. The MVAA shall award grants to support
8 efforts to connect veterans and their dependents with federal
9 compensation and pension benefits and state veterans' benefits,
10 including emergency grants through the Michigan veterans' trust
11 fund and other local or nonprofit assistance that may be available
12 to veterans and their dependents. The MVAA shall establish a
13 competitive grant process that satisfies all of the following:
14 (a) Utilizes a service provision model to provide services
15 across the state and can be tracked regionally to ensure that
16 veterans and their dependents in this state, including those within
17 tribal communities, are provided with services, advocacy, and
18 outreach as close to the communities in which they live as
19 possible.
