767
1 (b) Calculating resident member maintenance assessments in
2 order to accurately calculate resident member maintenance
3 assessments for each billing cycle and ensure that all past due
4 resident member maintenance assessments are addressed within 30
5 days.
6 (c) Monetary donations and donated goods.
7 (d) The handling of resident member funds to ensure the
8 release of funds within 15 calendar days upon the resident member
9 leaving the home and to ensure that a representative of a resident
10 member is provided a full accounting of that resident member's
11 funds within 30 calendar days after the death of that resident
12 member.
13 (e) Financial reporting and accounting.
14 Sec. 507. (1) The MVH shall post on its website the following:
15 (a) All policies adopted by the MVFA and the veterans'
16 facility related to the administrative operations of the veterans'
17 facility.
18 (b) The agenda and minutes of public meetings of the MVFA
19 board.
20 (2) The MVH shall provide a report with copies of each
21 veterans' facility's USDVA State Veteran Home quarterly report.
22 These quarterly reports shall also be posted on the MVH website and
23 these reports must include statistics and information that
24 demonstrates the performance of MVH compared to available state and
25 national veterans' homes or nursing homes.
26 (3) Not later than January 15, the MVH shall provide a report
27 on the following:
28 (a) Census data for each veterans' facility, including
29 information on level of care, service era of its resident members,
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

768
1 payer source, and average income and assessment rate.
2 (b) Per patient daily care hours provided by each veterans'
3 facility, by level of care.
4 (4) The MVH shall provide a bimonthly report on the financial
5 status of each veterans' facility and central MVFA/MVH
6 administration. Information shall include, but not be limited to,
7 actual year-to-date and projected year-end revenues and
8 expenditures, by fund source.
9 (5) The MVH shall provide a report on the results of any
10 annual or for-cause survey conducted by any entity with oversight
11 over the veterans' facility and any corresponding corrective action
12 plan. This information shall also be made available publicly
13 through the MVH website.
14 (6) In addition to the information required under section
15 12(1) of the Michigan veterans' facility authority act, 2016 PA
16 560, MCL 36.112, not later than January 31, the MVFA shall provide
17 a report detailing the strategies and actions taken to maximize
18 revenues from non-general fund sources and cost savings strategies.
19 Sec. 508. In addition to the funds appropriated in part 1,
20 private revenues held by the MVH on a nonfiduciary basis for a
21 resident member of a veterans' facility are appropriated to pay
22 medical expenses, member assessments, and other expenses incurred
23 by that resident member. Any unexpended or unencumbered private
24 revenues held on a nonfiduciary basis by the MVH at the close of
25 the fiscal year do not lapse to the general fund and must be
26 carried forward into the subsequent fiscal year.
27 Sec. 509. Not later than January 15 , the MVFA shall provide a
