3 Sec. 1301. (1) Funds appropriated in part 1A for Selfridge Air
4 National Guard Base must be used to support costs of runway
5 encroachment solutions while complying with air installation
6 compatible use zone program recommendations, including, but not
7 limited to, all of the following:
8 (a) Capital improvements necessary to shift the runway to the
9 north and repair the airfield and nonairfield features of the base
10 and surrounding community impacted by the shift.
11 (b) Infrastructure projects including, but not limited to,
12 roadways repairs, vehicle access to the base and to the museum,
13 stormwater drain and culvert repairs and modernization, force
14 protection features, airfield features, and taxiway extensions.
15 (2) Unexpended funds appropriated in part 1A for Selfridge Air
16 National Guard Base are designated as a work project appropriation.
17 Unencumbered or unallotted funds shall not lapse at the end of the
18 fiscal year and shall be available for expenditures under this
19 section until the project has been completed. The following is in
20 compliance with section 451a of the management and budget act, 1984
21 PA 431, MCL 18.1451a:
22 (a) The purpose of the project is to support costs of runway
23 encroachment solutions.
24 (b) The project will be accomplished by utilizing state
25 employees, contracts with service providers, or both.
26 (c) The total estimated cost of the project is
27 $152,000,000.00.
28 (d) The tentative completion date is September 30, 2027.
