3 Sec. 216. (1) A department or agency shall maximize
4 utilization of its in-person state workforce. A department or
5 agency shall prioritize occupancy utilization of office space for
6 each division within the department or agency. Employees with job
7 responsibilities that require the employees to serve in their
8 capacities outside of an office shall be monitored each pay period
9 to ensure all work hours reported on the timesheet were actually
10 worked.
11 (2) A department or agency shall comply with requirements set
12 forth by the office of the state employer on in-person work and
13 utilization and occupancy rates of state buildings to ensure in-
14 person work is optimized and occupancy rates are 80% or higher,
15 subject to market conditions.
16 (3) A department or agency shall adhere to civil service rules
17 and regulations that state the standard biweekly work period for a
18 full-time employee in the classified service of this state is the
19 equivalent of 80 hours of work. A department or agency shall
20 establish policies and processes to ensure all employees are
21 working their jobs during agreed-upon business hours.
22 Sec. 218. A department or agency receiving appropriations in
23 part 1 shall receive and retain copies of all reports funded from
24 appropriations in part 1. A department or agency shall follow
25 federal and state law and guidelines for short-term and long-term
26 retention of records. A department or agency may electronically
27 retain copies of reports unless otherwise required by federal and
28 state guidelines.
29 Sec. 219. Not later than April 1, the department shall report
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

864
1 on each specific policy change made to implement a public act
2 affecting the department that took effect during the previous
3 calendar year. The report must include a reference to the public
