26 Sec. 232. A department or agency that receives an
27 appropriation under this part or part 1 must provide an annual
28 report to the standard report recipients detailing federal policy
29 changes that do, or are expected to do, any of the following:
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

865
1 (a) Affect the operations of the department, including
2 reductions in federal revenue. For federal revenue reductions, the
3 annual report must detail the impact on the department or agency
4 and residents of this state, including, but not limited to, all of
5 the following information:
6 (i) The amount of additional state revenue required to replace
7 the lost federal revenue.
8 (ii) The services the department or agency will have to reduce
9 or eliminate due to the lost revenue.
10 (iii) The anticipated fiscal impact on residents of this state.
11 (b) Affect an industry, community, population, or other group
12 regulated or served by, or that otherwise engages with, the
13 department or agency.
14 (c) Create a regulatory gap that could negatively impact the
15 public.
16 (d) Increase the department's or agency's costs.
17 (e) Reduce or eliminate a program that provides services to
18 residents of this state.
