20 Sec. 303. (1) The department shall not utilize bridge bundling
21 contracting methods for projects involving the construction,
22 rehabilitation, or replacement of bridges delivered through the
23 local agency program unless all of the following conditions apply:
24 (a) A local agency program bridge bundling project package is
25 limited to a maximum of 5 bridges.
26 (b) A local agency program bridge bundling project package
27 must be confined to a single department region or limited to
28 contiguous counties.
29 (c) The department shall not impose any bidder qualification
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

871
1 requirements beyond standard prequalification. The department shall
2 not use requests for qualifications, statements of qualifications,
3 shortlisting, or other additional prerequisites for bidders.
4 (2) Bridge bundling for state trunkline or freeway projects
5 may be utilized where multiple structures are contiguous or nearly
6 contiguous, or if bundling is required for traffic control, cost
7 efficiency, or federal funding participation.
8 Sec. 304. If, as a requirement of bidding on a highway
9 project, the department requires a contractor to submit financial
10 or proprietary documentation as to how the bid was calculated, the
11 department shall keep that bid documentation confidential and shall
12 not disclose that bid documentation other than to a department
13 representative without the contractor's written consent. The
14 department may disclose the bid documentation if necessary to
15 address or defend a claim by a contractor.
16 Sec. 306. (1) The amounts appropriated in part 1 to support
17 tax and fee collection, law enforcement, and other program services
18 provided to the department and to transportation funds by other
19 state departments must be expended from transportation funds
20 pursuant to annual contracts between the department and those other
21 state departments. The contracts must be executed before the
22 expenditure or obligation of those funds. The contracts must
23 provide, but are not limited to, the following data applicable to
24 each state department:
25 (a) Estimated costs to be recovered from transportation funds.
26 (b) Description of services provided to the department and/or
27 transportation funds and financed with transportation funds.
28 (c) Detailed cost allocation methods appropriate to the type
29 of services being provided and the activities financed with
ERE S06102'26 (S-1) 9n6epi

872
1 transportation funds.
