1 Sec. 310. The department shall post in a timely manner copies
2 of the agenda, approved minutes, and audio recording of state
3 transportation commission meetings.
4 Sec. 313. (1) From funds appropriated in part 1, the
5 department may increase a state infrastructure bank program and
6 grant or loan funds in accordance with regulations of the state
7 infrastructure bank program of the United States Department of
8 Transportation. The department shall administer the state
9 infrastructure bank for the purpose of providing a revolving, self-
10 sustaining resource for financing transportation infrastructure
11 projects.
12 (2) In addition to funds provided in subsection (1), money
13 received by this state as federal grants, repayment of state
14 infrastructure bank loans, or other reimbursement or revenue
15 received by this state as a result of projects funded by the
16 program and interest earned on that money must be deposited in the
17 revolving state infrastructure bank fund and must be available for
18 transportation infrastructure projects. At the close of the fiscal
19 year, any unencumbered funds remaining in the state infrastructure
20 bank fund remain in the fund and carry forward into the succeeding
21 fiscal year.
22 (3) The department shall prepare a report on the status of the
23 state infrastructure bank and submit the report to the standard
24 report recipients on or before December 31, 2026. The report must
25 include all of the following:
26 (a) The balance in the state infrastructure bank on September
27 30, 2026, including a breakdown of the balance by cash and cash
28 equivalents, outstanding loans, and balance available for loan to
29 local agencies.
