5 Sec. 384. (1) Except as otherwise provided in subsection (2),
6 the department shall not obligate this state to expend any state
7 transportation revenue for construction planning or construction of
8 the Gordie Howe International Crossing or a renamed successor. In
9 addition, except as provided in subsection (2), the department
10 shall not commit this state to any new contract related to the
11 construction planning or construction of the Gordie Howe
12 International Crossing or a renamed successor that would obligate
13 this state to expend any state transportation revenue. An
14 expenditure for staff resources used in connection with project
15 activities that is subject to full and prompt reimbursement from
16 Canada is not considered an expenditure of state transportation
17 revenue.
18 (2) If the legislature enacts specific enabling legislation
19 for the construction of the Gordie Howe International Crossing or a
20 renamed successor, subsection (1) does not apply once the enabling
21 legislation goes into effect.
22 Sec. 385. (1) The department shall submit monthly reports to
23 the standard report recipients, the speaker of the house of
24 representatives, the house of representatives minority leader, the
25 senate majority leader, and the senate minority leader on all of
26 the following:
27 (a) All expenditures made by this state related to the Gordie
28 Howe Bridge.
